# Browser support matrix consumed by:
#   - @angular/build (output target features, polyfill set)
#   - autoprefixer (CSS vendor prefixes)
#   - postcss-preset-env / sass embedded autoprefixer (where applicable)
#
# Angular ships a default browserslist when this file is absent, but the
# default tracks caniuse-lite releases and drifts each upgrade. Pinning
# the matrix here makes any change to support semantics show up as an
# explicit edit to this file rather than a silent CSS-output diff.
#
# Target: "modern evergreen" — the last two majors of each evergreen engine
# plus Firefox ESR. Queried per-engine (rather than the broad `> 0.5%` /
# `last 2 versions`, which pull in QQ/UC/KaiOS/Opera-Mobile/old-Chrome) so the
# set stays inside Angular's official support matrix — no build-time
# "unsupported browser" warnings.
last 2 Chrome versions
last 2 Firefox versions
last 2 Edge versions
last 2 Safari versions
last 2 iOS versions
Firefox ESR
